    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "to be honest, I think it goes against common sense expectation. a public chat is an immutable record of conversations; if you left it and rejoined, you would fully expect to fetch its latest state including everything you seen before\r\n\r\n> delete it because you don't want some of those messages,\r\n\r\nI think the expectation is more like, you don't want to participate in it, it's about choosing to subscribe to a conversation\r\n\r\n_edit_: maybe to leave a more definite design consideration : the optimal UX here is what the issue author described as expected behaviour",
